          "topic": "CapEx and Compute Outlook",
          "content": "CapEx was $14.8B; full-year 2025 guidance is $60-65B with the biggest growth in servers, followed by data centers and networking, supporting generative AI, core AI, and long-term infrastructure; we expect to keep using servers ~5.5 years to lower depreciation."
        },
        {
          "topic": "Meta AI adoption and monetization path",
          "content": "Meta AI logged 700M MAUs, with WhatsApp leading usage for info, education, and emotional support; we are enhancing memory, personalization, and content recommendations while keeping monetization experiments focused on a great consumer experience and saving revenue ramps for once the product reaches massive scale."
        },
        {
          "topic": "Headcount and Productivity",
          "content": "Headcount grew 10% to ~74K, with nearly 90% of new hires in R&D and infrastructure; we expect additional technical hiring for infrastructure, monetization, Reality Labs, generative AI, and compliance while keeping business function hiring constrained, and we continue ramping AI coding assistants to boost engineer productivity."
        }
      ]
    }
